21/12/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Prime Minister Hashim Thaci on Saturday (December 20th) officially nominated General Sylejman Selimi as head of the Kosovo Security Force (KSF). Thaci presented the nomination to President Fatmir Sejdiu, who is due to sign the decree. The international community has been awaiting the appointment of the commander. Selimi has served as commander of the Kosovo Protection Corps, whose duties the KSF is assuming. (MIA, Focus - 20/12/08)
